goals.question: Is there a correlation between fertility rate and population?

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify if there is a positive or negative correlation between population and fertility rate.

goals.question: What is the trend of life expectancy over the years?

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the distribution of population across different clusters.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='life_expect', by='country', ax=ax)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across different countries?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.legend(title='Country', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['pop'], data['fertility'], c=data['cluster'], cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Population')
    ax.set_ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    ax.set_title('Is there a correlation between fertility rate and population?')
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Clusters")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.plot(data['year'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the trend of life expectancy over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Life Expectancy'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group by cluster and calculate the mean of life_expect and fertility
    cluster_means = data.groupby('cluster')[['life_expect', 'fertility']].mean()

    # Create a bar chart
    ax = cluster_means.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(10, 6))

    # Set the title
    plt.title('What is the average life expectancy and fertility rate of each cluster?', wrap=True)

    # Set the x-axis label
    plt.xlabel('Cluster')

    # Set the y-axis label
    plt.ylabel('Mean Values')

    # Add a legend
    plt.legend(['Life Expectancy', 'Fertility Rate'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
